channel.title: "High-Speed" internet
channel.description:
I'v had Embarq(now know as CenturyLink) high-speed internet for about a year now. I'v got the fastest internet they offer which is 10mbps.
Its been gradually getting slower and slower over the course of this year. Started out incredibly fast, then began having random moments when I would have to refresh a couple times. Now its became so slow that I cant even watch a youtube video without having to pause it for 20 minutes. I'v had dial-up twice as fast as this.
I called them today and all they said was we're sorry for the inconvenience and that everyones internet speed with them is slow around this area. I asked them to lower the monthly cost and they said "we will give you a compensation once we have fixed the problem" whatever that means...
I just cancelled with them and i'm most likely switching to Verizon's internet. What internet providers do you guys have? And what download / upload speeds are you getting?

item.description:
@R.I.P_RSC wrote:

The package should give me 25 up and 1.5 down, I (or my parents) pay €25 for internet, €9 for unlimited calls to all home numbers in Europe, and €17,50 for normal TV. A different ISP is building a glass fibre network in the whole country, and offers 100 down/100 up for €85 per month. It’s not available in my village though. My current ISP offers 120 down and 10 up, for only €50. Not bad, although the up-speed isn’t really in proportion. Too bad I’m not the one who decides…

item.title: "High-Speed" internet
item.dc:creator: @moparisthebest Moparisthebest
item.description:
@moparisthebest wrote:

When we moved here, my options were ‘high speed’ DSL, or dialup. Both were horribly slow, but Time Warner Cable was at the road and I had to dig a ~300ft long x 2ft deep ditch to run cable back to where it could reach my house. Now they have upgraded their service and I have 30mbps down and 5mbps up, which I get near to (like 27ish down, 4.5ish up), and it costs $50/month which is pretty high I think.

@edit, made a mistake on the upload speed, and put in a picture.
